<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0584 </DOCNO><TEXT>The article discusses the current situation of the Alkem nuclear company,its foundation, the hazards resulting for public health and the statefrom the processing of plutonium, the economic aspects of plutonium processingwhich are seen positive by the author, and the attitude of the SocialDemocratic Party, SPD, who clearly stated their 'out' for Alkem. Thecentral issue discussed by the author is the still not completed licensingprocedure and the relevant aspects of laws and rights involved. Somespeculations are presented regarding the future of Alkem, seen againstthe background of the existing political landscape in Hessen, and thelegal requirements given by the Atomic Energy Act. (HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>